<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL; NO NEED FOR A LIFT FOR ARIZONA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ray Owes scored 21 points and Damon Stoudamire had 19 Monday night to lead 
seventh-ranked Arizona to a 92-76 victory over La Salle at Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona Coach Lute Olson missed the game because of back problems caused while 
lifting weights.He was replaced by assistant Jim Rosborough as the Wildcats 
improved to 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 For La Salle (5-1), Kareem Townes scored 24 points. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 12 Maryland 120, Towson State 73 -- Keith Booth scored 18 points as the 
Terrapins (7-2) rolled over the Tigers (3-3) at College Park, Md. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 18 Michigan State 111, Cleveland State 68 -- Shawn Respert scored 27 
points to lead the Spartans (3-1) over the Vikings (2-3) at East Lansing, Mich. 
OTHER GAMES 
</P>
<P>
 Oregon State 72, Fresno State 67 -- Forwards Brent Barry and Mustapha Hoff 
both scored 25 points to lead the Beavers (3-2) over the Bulldogs (3-3) at 
Corvallis, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern 132, Faith Baptist 44 -- Tim Roberts made 10 three-point shots and 
scored a school-record 56 points to lead the Jaguars (2-0) over The Force (5-9) 
at Baton Rouge, La. 
</P>
<P>
 Faith Baptist, located in the small south Louisiana community of Church Point, 
is fielding a team for the first time this season. 
</P>
