<P>
USC ADDS MARINELLI TO COACHING STAFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rod Marinelli became USC's defensive line coach Monday, after coaching Arizona 
State's defensive line the last three seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Marinelli, 45, coached Cal's defensive line for nine seasons before joining 
Arizona State's staff in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 At USC, he succeeds Doug Smith, moved to the offensive line last week by Coach 
John Robinson. Marinelli joins the staff next week, with the Trojans preparing 
for their Cotton Bowl game against Texas Tech on Jan. 2. 
</P>
<P>
 Marinelli played football at Rosemead High and Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
