<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: BLOEMFONTEIN; ANC TAKING STOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Led by President Nelson Mandela, about 3,000 delegates from South Africa's 
ruling African National Congress, the black liberation 
movement-turned-political party, will meet Saturday through Wednesday to 
discuss how far they have come and the challenges that lie ahead in their 
country. 
</P>
<P>
 The 49th national conference will take place in Bloemfontein, where the ANC 
was founded in 1912. The city, capital of the old Orange Free State, later 
became a stronghold of the right-wing white Afrikaners who institutionalized 
racial segregation under apartheid. 
</P>
<P>
 The theme of the conference will be "From Resistance to Reconstruction and 
Nation-Building." 
</P>
<P>
 Despite reports of a leadership struggle, Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to win 
easy reelection as secretary general. 
</P>
