VENTURA COUNTY ROUNDUP: REDDI BRAKE INCREASES ITS SALES, RENEWS CREDIT LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reddi Brake Supply Corp., a Ventura firm that distributes auto parts to 
professional mechanics, reports increased November sales and the renewal of its 
bank credit line. 
</P>
<P>
 Same-store sales last month rose nearly 13% over the same period last year, 
the company says.And, thanks mainly to a more than threefold increase in its 
number of units, total sales last month increased 149%, to $3.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 An aggressive expansion drive has given the company 77 stores, compared with 
21 a year ago. New locations added last month are in Columbus, Ohio; Chicago; 
Gainesville, Fla.; Kansas City, Kan., and St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
 Reddi also announced that Sumitomo Bank of California has renewed its 
working-capital line of credit until Oct. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 Reddi distributes brake systems, chassis components and other parts. 
