WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUNEME; MAN SOUGHT IN BANK ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAN STEVENS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities are searching for a man who robbed a Bank of America office in 
Port Hueneme on Monday afternoon and fled with an unknown amount of cash. 
</P>
<P>
 Officer Ron Burns of the Port Hueneme Police Department said a man entered the 
bank branch at 755 W. Channel Islands Blvd. about 4:41 p.m. Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Burns said the man made it appear he had a handgun and handed a note to a 
teller demanding money. 
</P>
<P>
 Police searched the neighborhood but did not find the suspect. Burns said no 
one saw a weapon, and no one was hurt. The FBI is investigating. JAN STEVENS 
