<TEXT>
<P>
 Advanced Placement tests are offered in 16 subjects, including European 
history, calculus and physics. To become eligible for college credit, students 
must score at least 3 out of a possible 5 points on the test. The rate at which 
high school juniors and seniors qualified for college credit by taking the 
tests has more than tripled in the past decade. 
</P>
<P>
 For example, 10 years ago, the statewide percentage was 3.4%, meaning that 
fewer than four students per 100 earned college credit. 
</P>
