METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
DEPUTY SHOT BY MAN ON SKATEBOARD HAS SURGERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Los Angeles County sheriff's deputy shot in the head by a skateboarder who 
later committed suicide underwent surgery Monday to clean a head wound, a 
hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Steven Belanger, 29, was shot in the head and foot Saturday after stopping a 
car that contained the suspect in an assault incident, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Katherine Koetters, a spokeswoman for Queen of the Valley Hospital in West 
Covina, said Belanger was operated on to remove bone fragments from his head. 
She could not say whether doctors also attempted to remove the bullet lodged in 
his head. 
</P>
<P>
 Belanger had stopped a car in Rowland Heights containing Gregory D. Powell, 
18, and a teen-age girl, authorities said. The officer recognized Powell as a 
suspect in an incident involving an assault with a deadly weapon. 
</P>
<P>
 After handcuffing Powell and placing him in the patrol car, Belanger was 
questioning the girl when a friend of Powell's, 20-year-old Matthew Hagemann, 
cruised up on his skateboard and shot the officer, authorities said. Hagemann 
later fatally shot himself in the head. 
</P>
