<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Literacy Volunteers of America of the Buena Park Library were commended by 
the city recently for helping hundreds of adults learn to speak, read and write 
English. 
</P>
<P>
 From July, 1993, to July, 1994, the volunteers spent 3,839 hours tutoring 44 
adults ranging in age from 25 to 60.That work would have earned the tutors 
about $49,907 if they had charged current market rates. 
</P>
<P>
 The tutors may also be helping to bring down the crime rate. About 80% of the 
felons in California jails today are illiterate, according to the Literacy 
Volunteers. 
</P>
<P>
 No one is required to have specialized education to be a tutor -- just the 
ability to read and write English and the desire to help others learn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
