<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; POLICE IDENTIFY DEAD NAKED JUMPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who died Sunday after jumping naked from a second-story hotel balcony 
and then running from police was identified by investigators Monday as Gregory 
Lee Jensen, 37, of Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of his death is unknown, pending toxicological tests, Orange County 
Sheriff's Lt. Dan Martini said."There was a number of conditions suggesting 
that he may have been under the influence," Martini said. "His behavior was 
quite bizarre." 
</P>
<P>
 Officers said they saw him standing naked on the balcony of Friendship Beach 
Inn in the 18100 block of Beach Boulevard about 4:30 p.m. Sunday. After they 
ordered him several times to return to the hotel room, Jensen jumped off the 
balcony onto a parked car, crushing its roof and shattering the rear window, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jensen then ran west on Beach Boulevard, police said. Officers chased him 
across the street and used pepper spray in an attempt to restrain him. The 
spray had little effect on Jensen, who continued running, Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jensen finally fell to one knee on the sidewalk, where officers pinned him and 
handcuffed him. Paramedics arrived and noticed that he was having trouble 
breathing and took him to Huntington Beach Medical Center, where he later died. 
</P>
<P>
 Jensen was registered as a guest at the Friendship Beach Inn, according to 
police. Neither he nor the hotel would say when he checked in or whether he was 
alone. THAO HUA 
</P>
</TEXT>
