<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A collection of rare and antique dolls, puppets and toys from around the world 
will be on display from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the Bowers Museum of Cultural Art 
in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 The dolls are made from materials including china, bisque, papier-mache and 
wood. One wax doll from the 1920s, the Bye-Lo Baby, is considered to be one of 
the finest examples of realistic doll-making. 
</P>
<P>
 The museum is at 2002 N. Main St. Information: (714) 567-3600. 
</P>
</TEXT>
