<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 3% WATER RATE INCREASE EXPECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Customers of Calleguas Water District will probably see a rate increase of 
about 3% next year, General Manager Donald R. Kendall said. 
</P>
<P>
 The district supplies water to about 75% of the residential customers in 
Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 Kendall said an expected increase of between 6% and 10% was averted by a 
restructuring of the rates by the Metropolitan Water District. 
</P>
<P>
 The additional revenue will pay for capital improvements to the water system, 
including a second feeder line to back up the main line that brings Northern 
California water to Calleguas customers. 
</P>
<P>
 The exact amount of the increase will be set by the Metropolitan Water 
District board this month, finalized in March and take effect in July, Kendall 
said. IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</TEXT>
