<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: WESTLAKE VILLAGE; CITY WILL RECYCLE OLD CHRISTMAS TREES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Westlake Village is asking its residents to think green by 
recycling their evergreens. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting Dec. 27, Christmas trees can be discarded in trash bins at Bennett 
Park, 31800 Village Center Road, and City Hall, 4373 Park Terrace Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 The recycled trees will be turned into chips for mulch used in weed abatement 
and erosion control, according to the city planning director's office. 
</P>
<P>
 The trees should be stripped of metal stands and decorations, so far as 
possible. For information, call (818) 706-1613. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
