<P>
BLOOD DRIVE SCHEDULED AT DANA HILLS HIGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Associated Student Union at Dana Hills High School is sponsoring a blood 
drive Wednesday in the school's gymnasium. 
</P>
<P>
 Blood donated during the 7 a.m.-to-1 p.m. drive will go to the local Red 
Cross. Donors must be at least 17 years old and weigh a minimum of 110 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Regular or first-time donors are encouraged to contact the school at (714) 
496-6666. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills High School is at 33333 Street of the Golden Lantern. 
