<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT'S THE DEAL: BODY WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN DOHENY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When pimples erupt on teen- or middle-aged faces, the goal is obliteration -- 
or at the very least, cover-up.The options and the fees: 
</P>
<P>
 * Retin-A acne cream, .025% strength, 20-gram tube, by prescription only, 
$35.90. 
</P>
<P>
 * Oxy-10 acne medicine, 1 ounce, $6.49. 
</P>
<P>
 * Stridex acne gel, 1 ounce, $4.99. 
</P>
<P>
 * Brown paper bag, pack of 50, house brand, $1.11. KATHLEEN DOHENY 
</P>
</TEXT>
