<P>
VIOLENCE IN PAKISTAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gunmen killed four more people, including a police officer, pushing the death 
toll from mounting violence to 80 in 12 days, police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 650 people have been killed this year in Karachi, where sectarian, 
ethnic and factional feuding has spun out of control. 
