<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY IN BANKRUPTCY; PROPERTY TAX PROCESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here are the steps that a property tax payment goes through before ending up 
as, among other things, a county employee's paycheck. 
</P>
<P>
 * County tax collector staff opens payment envelopes. 
</P>
<P>
 * Staff member encodes dollar amount on check, records payment on magnetic 
tape. 
</P>
<P>
 * Tax collector can research property questions as soon as one day after 
payment is recorded. 
</P>
<P>
 * Coded checks are deposited in county's undesignated funds bank account. 
</P>
<P>
 * Checks are transferred to second bank account which covers payroll and 
expenses. PROPERTY TAXING TREND 
</P>
<P>
 The amount of property taxes collected in Orange County has declined recently. 
</P>
<P>
 1994-95*: 97.7 
</P>
<P>
 * estimated CREDIT COUNSELING 
</P>
<P>
 Consumer Credit Counseling Service of Orange County, a nonprofit organization, 
is offering emergency planning for anyone whose personal finances are likely to 
be hurt by the county's bankruptcy filing. For more information, call (714) 
544-8880. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Orange County auditor's office  
</P>
<P>
 Researched by JEFF BEAN and APRIL JACKSON / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
