<TEXT>
<P>
 Seventeen inmates have escaped from a Mexican prison near Texas through an 
elaborate tunnel dug beneath a prison wall. 
</P>
<P>
 The men took three to six months to dig a tunnel almost 80 yards long from a 
cell in the CeReSo prison to a nearby orchard, police said. They escaped early 
