<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY COLLEGE RECEIVER TO SIGN WITH CAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brian Comer, an All-American receiver from Valley College, said Monday he will 
sign to play football at Cal. 
</P>
<P>
 Comer, who caught 81 passes for 1,753 yards and 15 touchdowns in 11 games this 
season, said he had also scheduled recruiting visits to Wyoming and UNLV, but 
he canceled those after deciding on Cal. 
</P>
<P>
 Comer said he chose the school "because I will be challenged in the classroom 
academically and will be challenged athletically on the field." 
</P>
<P>
 A 5-foot-11, 180-pound sophomore, Comer holds the Valley College career 
records for receptions (139), yardage (2,657) and touchdowns (26). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange County Bowl earlier this month, he caught 10 passes for 205 
yards and two touchdowns, leading Valley to a 36-28 victory against Rancho 
Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
 While at Chatsworth High, he was an All-City Section quarterback. During his 
senior year in 1991, he passed for 1,125 yards, leading area City quarterbacks. 
He redshirted at Valley in 1992, still trying to play quarterback, and was then 
moved to receiver to make room for Sean Fitzgerald, who now plays at 
Pittsburgh. JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
