<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 7; Column 2; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
145 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
49ERS SUSPEND O'KELLEY FOR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON REID 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior forward Terrance O'Kelley, whose academic performance has disappointed 
Long Beach State Coach Seth Greenberg, was suspended Monday for one game, the 
school announced. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Kelley, 6 feet 7 and 245 pounds, will miss the 49ers' nonconference game 
Dec. 21 against Montana at The Pyramid.O'Kelley remains in good academic 
standing at Long Beach and is eligible according to Big West Conference and 
NCAA standards. 
</P>
<P>
 "Terrance didn't tell us the truth (about his academic situation)," Greenberg 
said. "You don't lie to people who care about you." 
</P>
<P>
 O'Kelley did not start the season opener against Detroit Mercy for failure to 
turn in a class project. He is averaging 6.6 points and five rebounds for the 
49ers (2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 As a junior, O'Kelley was selected third-team all-conference. He averaged 11.9 
points, 6.8 rebounds and a team-leading 2.2 blocks. JASON REID 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121394-0212 </DOCNO>
