<HEADLINE>
<P>
OETTINGER DECIDES TO ATTEND STANFORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Foothill's Tara Oettinger said Monday she has signed a letter of intent to 
attend Stanford. 
</P>
<P>
 Oettinger, The Times' Orange County girls' track and field athlete of the year 
last season, said she considered only one other school, Cornell, because her 
brother, Ryan, went there. 
</P>
<P>
 "I really liked it," she said, "but I didn't want to go to school in the 
East." 
</P>
<P>
 As a junior last season, Oettinger won four events at the Orange County 
Championships and became the school's first State champion by winning the long 
jump at 19 feet 7 1/2 inches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
