<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; WOIMBERGHE'S TWO GOALS SPARK CYPRESS IN SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michelle Woimberghe's second goal of the game with about 10 minutes to play 
gave Cypress a 3-2 victory over Fountain Valley Monday in the title game of the 
Magnolia girls' soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Jane Specht added one goal for Cypress (6-1-1). Mindy Miller scored twice for 
Fountain Valley (6-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 3, Cerritos Gahr 2 -- Heather Gibson scored all three goals and Lyndsay 
Bishop recorded eight saves for Sonora (5-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In a nonleague game: 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 2, San Diego University of San Diego High 0 -- Cassie Campbell and 
Kristen Palmer each scored one goal and Jennifer Simmons recorded six saves to 
lead Marina (2-0) in its 40th consecutive game without a loss. University, the 
defending San Diego Section Division III champion, is 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica 6, Westminster 2 -- Graig Chow scored four goals, three in the first 
half, for visiting Pacifica (3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Bolsa Grande girls' basketball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande 41, Laguna Beach 40 -- Jill Tantardini put back Lien Mai's missed 
free throw with five seconds left to give Bolsa Grande (2-4) the victory. Thao 
Dong led the Matadors with a game-high 18 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia 61, Long Beach Wilson 53 -- Andrea Picchi, who had 20 points and 13 
rebounds, made six of six free throws in the fourth quarter for Magnolia (5-0) 
in a first-round game. Stacy Tewell added 19 points and eight rebounds for 
Magnolia. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills 66, Santa Ana 46 -- Dyanna Hatch scored 26 points and Sarah 
Warnick added 24 to lead Trabuco Hills in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Cypress tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 59, Rancho Alamitos 43 -- Naomi Morales had 13 points and 12 rebounds 
for Katella (3-4) in a consolation game. Jamie Howard scored 13 points for 
Rancho Alamitos (0-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In the El Dorado tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 63, Pomona Ganesha 32 -- Jamie Nebeker scored 16 points, including 
two three-pointers for host El Dorado (3-0). 
</P>
