<TEXT>
<P>
 Kmart Cuts 900 Jobs: The Troy, Mich.-based retailer, under pressure from 
investors to reduce expenses, cut the full-time jobs and launched a 
reorganization of its New Jersey-based fashion facility. Kmart Corp. Chairman 
Joseph Antonini said the layoffs, affecting almost every department at Kmart's 
international headquarters, are part of the company's efforts to reduce 
expenses to $600 million from $800 million by 1996. 
</P>
