</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lincoln National to Buy Delaware Management: The company said it signed a 
definitive agreement to acquire closely held Delaware Management Holdings Inc. 
for about $510 million, including the assumption of $209 million of debt.The 
transaction also provides for a contingency payment of $22.5 million based on 
future revenue growth. The shareholder selling the largest stake of 
Philadelphia-based Delaware Management Holdings, an investment adviser firm, is 
an investment partnership managed by New York merchant bank Castle Harlan Inc. 
Ft. Wayne, Ind.-based Lincoln National Corp. is the holding company for a group 
of insurance and financial services businesses. 
</P>
