<P>
 S&L Profits Hit 18-Month High: As interest rates rose, profits for the savings 
and loan industry increased $280 million in the third quarter to the highest 
level in 18 months.The Office of Thrift Supervision said S&Ls earned $1.52 
billion in the July-September quarter, compared to $1.24 billion in the 
previous three months. With short-term interest rates continuing to climb, 
thrifts paid out 3.63% of their assets in interest expenses, compared to 3.42% 
for the second quarter. Interest income rose more slowly in the third quarter, 
to 6.49% of assets from 6.35%. 
