<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOTHEBY'S TO PREVIEW TWO COLLECTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An auction preview exhibition of works from the Cyril Humphris collection and 
Old Master paintings from the New York Historical Society is on view at 
Sotheby's Beverly Hills showroom today through Thursday, 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Humphris, a leading London dealer and collector of Renaissance and later 
European sculpture, is selling 331 works from his holding at Sotheby's New York 
on Jan. 10-11. 
</P>
<P>
 Paintings from the financially troubled New York Historical Society will go on 
the block on Jan. 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Preview highlights include a 1598 marble sculpture of Adonis and a hound by 
Giovanni Bandini, valued at over $2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The exhibition is at 308 N. Rodeo Drive, Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 274-0340. 
</P>
