<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: FIRST AMERICAN FINANCIAL TO BUY TWO COMPANIES FOR $32 
MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First American Financial Corp. said Monday it has agreed to buy a mortgage 
credit reporting company and a flood threat data-service firm for a total of 
$32 million in cash and debt securities. 
</P>
<P>
 The real estate financial services company, based in Santa Ana, said it will 
acquire Credco Inc., a mortgage credit firm, from U.S. Bancorp of Portland, 
Ore. 
</P>
<P>
 First American also will acquire Flood Data Services Inc. of Austin, Texas, 
from a group led by the company's founder, Don Craven. Flood Data maintains a 
national database that shows where property flood zones can be found. 
</P>
<P>
 First American provides title insurance, tax monitoring and other services to 
property buyers and mortgage lenders. The transactions are expected to close in 
January. 
</P>
