REGIONAL ROUNDUP: CANOGA PARK FIRM ASKS FOR STOCK PROBE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Styles on Video Inc., a Canoga Park maker of computer imaging systems for hair 
salons, said it asked the American Stock Exchange to investigate recent trading 
of its stock for possible attempts to manipulate the price. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it believes that short selling might have occurred that 
violates Securities and Exchange regulations. In a short sale, an investor 
borrows stock and sells it, hoping the price will decline so the investor can 
repurchase the stock at the lower price and garner a profit. 
