<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CALIFORNIA AMPLIFIER SEES 3RD-QUARTER PROFITS JUMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California Amplifier Inc., a Camarillo-based maker of components used to 
receive television signals, reported a sharp increase in profit for its third 
quarter, which ended Nov. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 The company posted net income of $714,000, up 28% from $558,000 in the same 
three-month period a year earlier.Sales increased by 3% to $11.7 million, 
compared to $11.4 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For its nine-month period, the company reported profit of $1.67 million on 
sales of $34.2 million, compared to a year-earlier profit of $1.64 million on 
revenue of $30.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
 California Amplifier attributed its improved results to surging sales of its 
wireless cable television products, which include antennas and other components 
used to receive and convert microwave television signals. Sales of wireless 
cable products totaled $5.59 million in the third quarter, up 19% from a year 
earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
