<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: 4/FLIGHT INDUSTRIES AND AERO-DESIGN PLAN MERGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aero-design Technology Inc. and 4/Flight Industries, two Valencia companies 
that make products for the airline industry, said they have signed a letter of 
intent to merge. 
</P>
<P>
 Aero-design makes in-flight trash compactors for commercial airlines, and 
4/Flight makes galleys, crew rests and seating products for the commercial 
airline and general aviation markets.Both companies are privately held, and 
terms of the merger were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our products complement one another, and we will be able to do a better job 
of serving our worldwide customers with the combined resources of two 
companies," said John Wetzel, president and chief executive of Aero-design. 
</P>
<P>
 Wetzel will be president and chief executive following the merger, a spokesman 
said. Mike Hanks, president and chief executive of 4/Flight, will also stay 
with the company, and will be responsible for supervising the company's 
marketing strategies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
