<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jennifer Garrett, Capistrano Valley, Senior 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball/Center 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley Coach Pete Belanto was hoping to win at least two games in 
the South Coast Holiday Classic, but thanks largely to Garrett, the Cougars won 
four and the title. Garrett, who averaged 19 points and 16.5 rebounds, 
dominated the tournament."She pretty much carried us," Belanto said. "She was 
going to be the most valuable player of the tournament even if we didn't win 
it." Garrett, who is 6 feet 3, had nine points and 15 rebounds in a 43-38 
victory over Trabuco Hills in the title game. Trabuco Hills limited her 
offensive output by double-teaming her, but she compensated in other ways. "She 
still made good passes," Belanto said. "She rebounded and did other things to 
help us win." Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Kiyoko Miller 
</P>
<P>
 * Brea-Olinda, junior. Had 18 points and eight steals in the Ladycats' 64-42 
victory over Torrance Bishop Montgomery in the title game of the Ladycat 
Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 Deanna Mitchelson 
</P>
<P>
 * Aliso Niguel, sophomore. Averaged 27 points and 23 rebounds in three games 
in the South Coast Holiday Classic. Soccer 
</P>
<P>
 Marie Dillon 
</P>
<P>
 * El Modena, senior. Named the most valuable goalkeeper of the Vanguard Cup 
after she had seven saves in a 2-1 victory over Esperanza in the title game. 
</P>
<P>
 Kimberly Engesser 
</P>
<P>
 * Ocean View, senior. Scored three goals in the unranked Seahawks' victories 
over No. 6 Edison and No. 2 Mater Dei. 
</P>
